        #   - :region [Region] The region for the patient. Needed if visit is virtual.
        #   - :payer [Payer] The payer to consider when filtering by credentials.
        #   - :capabilities [Array<Capability>] Additional capabilities to consider when filtering by capabilities.
        #   - :mode [Array<String] The mode of the appointment type needed (in_person, virtual, phone).
        #   - :duration [Integer] The duration of the appointment type needed.
        #   - :communication_assistance [String] The communication assistance needed for the appointment type.
        #   - :limit_to_accepting_new_patients [Boolean] Limit to only staffers accepting new patients
        #
        # @return [<Calendaring::AvailableTime::Slot::Collection] An array of available time slots.
        #
        # @example
        #   times(
        #     appointment_type: AppointmentType.therapy_initial_session,
        #     date_range: Date.today..(Date.today + 7),
        #     timezone: "Eastern Time (US & Canada)",
        #     filters: { clinics: Clinic.find_by(name: "Brooklyn"), region: Region.new_jersey }
        #   )
        #
        # TODO: Make method may warn if the date range is too large and suggest making a `dates` call first.
        def times(root_appointment_type:, date_range:, timezone:, filters:)
          filters = Calendaring::AvailabilityFilters.from_filters(filters)

          appointment_types = root_appointment_type.filtered_appointment_types(**filters.for_appointment_types)
          AvailableTimes::Slot::Collection.new(
            appointment_types.flat_map do |appointment_type|
              staffers = Calendaring::CapableStaffers.new(appointment_type:, **filters.for_staffers).all

              # Check individual staffer flags
              template_staffers = staffers.select { |staffer| use_reef_templates_for_staffer?(staffer) }
              non_template_staffers = staffers - template_staffers

              results = []
              results += AvailableTimes.new(appointment_type:, date_range:, staffers: non_template_staffers, timezone:).all if non_template_staffers.any?
              if template_staffers.any?
                results += AvailableTimesFromTemplate.new(appointment_type:, date_range:, staffers: template_staffers, timezone:).all
              end
              results
            end
          )
        end

        # Finds available dates for a given appointment type within a specified date range and region.
        #
        # @param root_appointment_type [AppointmentType|RootAppointmentType] The appointment type or root appointment type. If root appointment type, filters can narrow down which children selected.
        # @param date_range [Range<Date> | Array<Date>] The range of dates to search within.
        # @param timezone [ActiveSupport::TimeZone | String] The timezone to consider when finding available dates. If string is provided,
        #   it should be in Rails timezone format.
        # @param filters [Hash|Calendaring::AvailabilityFilters] Additional filters to apply when searching for available dates.
        #   - :clinics [Array<Clinic>|Clinic] Array of clinic locations to filter by. Can also pass a single clinic object
        #   - :staffers [Array<Staffer>] Specific staffers to consider.
        #   - :region [Region] The region for the patient. Needed if visit is virtual.
        #   - :payer [Payer] The payer to consider when filtering by credentials.
        #   - :capabilities [Array<Capability>] Additional capabilities to consider when filtering by capabilities.
        #   - :mode [Array<String] The mode of the appointment type needed (in_person, virtual, phone).
        #   - :duration [Integer] The duration of the appointment type needed.
        #   - :communication_assistance [String] The communication assistance needed for the appointment type.
        #   - :limit_to_accepting_new_patients [Boolean] Limit to only staffers accepting new patients
        #
        # @return [<Calendaring::AvailableDates::AvailableDate::Collection] An array of available dates.
        #
        # @example
        #   dates(
        #     appointment_type: AppointmentType.therapy_initial_session,
        #     date_range: Date.today..(Date.today + 30),
        #     timezone: "Eastern Time (US & Canada)",
        #     filters: { clinics: Clinic.find_by(name: "Brooklyn"), region: Region.new_jersey }
        #   )
        #
        # Use this method when you need to know which days have availability without needing specific time slots.
        # This is more efficient for longer date ranges where you're initially just looking for available days.
        def dates(root_appointment_type:, date_range:, timezone:, filters:)
          # This won't be quite right with the new template system -- Getting dates isn't easy do do in bulk separately from getting time. Instead
          # will focus on ways of approximating or fetching first available date.

          filters = Calendaring::AvailabilityFilters.from_filters(filters)

          appointment_types = root_appointment_type.filtered_appointment_types(**filters.for_appointment_types)

          AvailableDates::AvailableDate::Collection.new(
            appointment_types.flat_map do |appointment_type|
              staffers = Calendaring::CapableStaffers.new(appointment_type:, **filters.for_staffers).all
              AvailableDates.new(appointment_type:, date_range:, staffers:, timezone:).all
            end
          )
        end

        # Finds staffers capable of handling a given appointment type based on specified filters.
        #
        # @param root_appointment_type [AppointmentType|RootAppointmentType] The appointment type or root appointment type. If root appointment type, filters can narrow down which children selected.
        # @param filters [Hash|Calendaring::AvailabilityFilters] Additional filters to apply when searching for capable staffers.
        #   - :clinics [Array<Clinic>|Clinic] Array of clinic locations to filter by. Can also pass a single clinic object
        #   - :region [Region] The region for the patient. Needed if visit is virtual.
        #   - :payer [Payer] The payer to consider when filtering by credentials.
        #   - :capabilities [Array<Capability>] Additional capabilities to consider when filtering by capabilities.
        #   - :mode [Array<String] The mode of the appointment type needed (in_person, virtual, phone).
        #   - :duration [Integer] The duration of the appointment type needed.
        #   - :communication_assistance [String] The communication assistance needed for the appointment type.
        #   - :limit_to_accepting_new_patients [Boolean] Limit to only staffers accepting new patients
        #
        # @return [Array<Staffer>] A unique array of staffers capable of handling the specified appointment type with the given filters.
        #
        # @example
        #   capable_staffers(
        #     root_appointment_type: RootAppointmentType.therapy_diagnostic_evaluation,
        #     filters: { clinics: Clinic.find_by(name: "Brooklyn"), region: Region.new_jersey }
        #   )
        def capable_staffers(root_appointment_type:, filters: {})
          filters = Calendaring::AvailabilityFilters.from_filters(filters)
          appointment_types = root_appointment_type.filtered_appointment_types(**filters.for_appointment_types)

          appointment_types.flat_map do |appointment_type|
            Calendaring::CapableStaffers.new(appointment_type:, **filters.for_staffers).all
          end.uniq
        end

        def use_reef_templates_for_staffer?(staffer)
          raise ArgumentError.new("staffer required") unless staffer.present?
          staffer.has_capability?(Capability.therapy) || Flipper.enabled?(:use_reef_templates, staffer)
        end
      end
    end
  end
end

module Members
  class AppointmentsController < BaseController
    include AcuityAppointmentSchedulable
    include CareCaseFiltered

    def show
      respond_to do |format|
        format.ics do
          appointment = current_account.appointments.find(params[:id])
          add_to_calendar = Calendaring::AddToCalendar.new(appointment)

          filename = "brightline_#{appointment.appointment_type_id}_#{appointment.start_time.strftime("%Y_%m_%d")}.ics"
          send_data(add_to_calendar.ical_data, filename: filename)
        rescue ActiveRecord::RecordNotFound => _e
          head 404
        end
        format.html do
          @appointment = current_account.appointments.find(params[:id])
          @session_details = current_account_member.teen? ? ::Appointments::TeenSessionDetails.new(@appointment) : ::Appointments::SessionDetails.new(@appointment)
          care_case_context = Family::CareCaseContext.new(care_cases: current_account_member.ordered_care_cases)
          @index = care_case_context.index_for_care_case_id(@appointment.care_case_id)
        end
      end
    end

    def index
      scope = (params[:tab] == "completed") ? "past" : "upcoming"

      @appointments = Appointment.where(care_case: current_accessible_care_cases).public_send(scope).not_canceled.chronological

      Analytics::Event::AppointmentsPage::Viewed.track(account_id: current_account.id)
    end

    def edit
      @appointment = Appointment.where(
        care_case: current_accessible_care_cases + current_pending_care_cases
      ).find(params[:id])

      if @appointment.within_24_hours? && !@appointment.canceled?
        return redirect_to members_appointments_path, flash: {
          notice: "Appointment cannot be rescheduled less than 24 hours before starting."
        }
      end

      @appointment_member = appointment_member
      @availability_data = Calendaring::Appointment::Availability::Data.new(
        date: date,
        slots: available_appointments
      )
    end

    def bookable
      @appointment = Appointment.find(params[:appointment_id])
      @book_appointment_path = book_appointment_path
    rescue Acuity::Api::Client::Error => e
      render_scheduling_error(e, appointment_name: appointment_name)
    end

    private

    def date
      @date ||= initial_request? ? first_available_date(min_date: min_reschedulable_date) : Date.parse(params[:date])
    end

    def initial_request?
      !params[:date].present?
    end

    def min_reschedulable_date
      ::Appointments::ReschedulationRules.new(appointment: @appointment).min_reschedulable_date
    end

    def available_appointments
      Calendaring::AvailableAppointments.new(
        date: date,
        availability_context: availability_context,
        availability_request_reporter: availability_request_reporter
      )
    end

    def availability_context
      Calendaring::AvailabilityContext.new(
        appointment_type: @appointment.appointment_type,
        care_case: @appointment.care_case,
        member: appointment_member,
        staffers: [@appointment.staffer],
        request_context: Calendaring::AvailabilityRequestContext.appointment_rescheduling,
        interpretation_language_id: @appointment.interpretation_language_id
      )
    end

    def appointment_member
      # this can be refactored once members have been backfilled on appointments
      @appointment_member ||= begin
        appt_member = @appointment.member
        return appt_member if appt_member.present?

        acuity_appointment = Acuity::Api::Appointment.find(@appointment.acuity_appointment_id)
        @appointment.care_case.members.find_by(
          first_name: acuity_appointment.first_name,
          last_name: acuity_appointment.last_name
        )
      end
    end

    def availability_request_reporter
      if initial_request?
        Calendaring::AppointmentAvailabilityRequestReporter.from_availability_context(availability_context)
      else
        Calendaring::NoopAvailabilityRequestReporter.new
      end
    end

    def book_appointment_path
      members_care_case_appointment_reschedulations_path(@appointment.care_case, @appointment)
    end

    def appointment_name
      Calendaring::AppointmentNameFromType.find(@appointment.appointment_type_id)
    end
  end
end

module Members
  module Appointments
    class ReschedulationsController < BaseController
      include CareCaseScoped

      def create
        Calendaring::MemberReschedulation.save!(appointment: current_appointment, start_time: selected_datetime, staffer: selected_staffer)
        redirect_to members_appointments_path, flash: {success: success_message}
      rescue Acuity::Api::Client::Error => e
        render_rescheduling_error(e)
      rescue => error
        Sentry.capture_exception(error)
        redirect_to members_appointments_path, flash: {error: error_message(error)}
      end

      private

      def selected_datetime
        Time.zone.parse(params.fetch(:appointment_datetime))
      end

      def current_appointment
        @current_appointment ||= current_care_case.appointments.find(params[:appointment_id])
      end

      def appointment_name
        Calendaring::AppointmentNameFromType.find(current_appointment.appointment_type_id)
      end

      def selected_staffer
        Staffer.find(params[:staffer_id]) if params[:staffer_id].present?
      end

      def render_rescheduling_error(error)
        raise error if BrightlineStack.development?
        alert_member_support
        Sentry.capture_exception(error)
        render(Members::Appointments::ErrorComponent.new(
          header: "Something went wrong",
          line_1: "We weren't able to reschedule that appointment for you.",
          line_2: "We have been informed about the error and are actively working on it."
        ))
      end

      def alert_member_support
        return if incomplete_reminder_exists?

        create_reminder
      end

      def create_reminder
        TaskManagement::Reminder.create!(
          reminder_attributes.merge(due_date: Time.zone.now)
        )
      end

      def incomplete_reminder_exists?
        TaskManagement::Reminder.where(
          group: :member_support,
          care_case: current_care_case,
          subject: current_appointment,
          completed_at: nil
        ).exists?
      end

      def reminder_attributes
        {
          title: "Member was unable to reschedule #{appointment_name}",
          group: :member_support,
          account: current_care_case.account,
          care_case: current_care_case,
          subject: current_appointment
        }
      end

      def success_message
        I18n.t("members.appointments.reschedulations.success_message")
      end

      def error_message(error)
        member_support_contact = Settings.contact_info.member_support

        I18n.t("members.appointments.reschedulations.error_message", member_support_contact_email: member_support_contact.email, member_support_contact_phone: member_support_contact.phone, error_message: error.message)
      end
    end
  end
end

module Members
  module Intake
    class CareGuideAppointmentsController < BaseController
      include CareCaseScoped

      BOOKING_WINDOW = Settings.care_guide.appointment_booking_window.days

      layout "members/onboarding"
      navigation_disabled
      show_nav_links [:home]

      def new
        load_week_availability
      end

      def edit
        @existing_appointment = existing_appointment
        load_week_availability
      end

      def selectable
        load_week_availability(week_start: params["date"].to_date.beginning_of_week)

        track_selectable_analytics(interpretation_language_id)

        respond_to do |format|
          format.turbo_stream do
            render turbo_stream: [
              turbo_stream.replace(
                :care_guide_display_area,
                Members::Intake::CareGuide::DisplayComponent.new(
                  date: params["date"].to_date,
                  availability_context: @availability_context,
                  slots_by_date_hash: @slots_by_date_hash,
                  existing_appointment:
                ).render_in(view_context)
              )
            ]
          end
        end
      end

      def availability
        load_week_availability(week_start: params["date"].to_date.beginning_of_week)
        respond_to do |format|
          format.turbo_stream do
            render turbo_stream: [
              turbo_stream.replace(
                :care_guide_display_area,
                Members::Intake::CareGuide::DisplayComponent.new(
                  date: params["date"].to_date,
                  availability_context: @availability_context,
                  slots_by_date_hash: @slots_by_date_hash,
                  existing_appointment:
                ).render_in(view_context)
              )
            ]
          end
        end
      end

      private

      helper_method def care_guide_appointment
        interpretation_language_id.present? ? AppointmentType.care_guide_session_with_interpretation : AppointmentType.care_guide_session
      end

      def care_guide_root_appointment_type
        AppointmentType.care_guide_session.root_appointment_type
      end

      def interpretation_language_id
        params["interpretation_language_id"]
      end

      def booked_care_guide_with_another_child?
        return false unless account.children.count > 1

        account.appointments
          .with_service_line(ServiceLine.care_guide)
          .with_status([AppointmentStatus.scheduled, AppointmentStatus.completed])
          .where.not(care_case: current_care_case)
          .exists?
      end

      def account
        current_member.accounts.first
      end

      def assigned_care_guide
        account.assigned_care_guide
      end

      def trapdoor
        members_care_case_triage_terminal_screen_path(current_care_case, "no_providers_available")
      end

      def book_with_another_care_guide_modal?
        as_boolean(params["book_with_another_care_guide_modal"])
      end

      def track_selectable_analytics(language_id)
        if language_id.present?
          Analytics::Event::CareGuideBookingInterpretation::Language::Selected.track(
            care_case: @availability_context.care_case,
            interpretation_language: Language.find(language_id).name
          )
        else
          Analytics::Event::CareGuideBookingInterpretation::Language::Removed.track(
            care_case: @availability_context.care_case
          )
        end
      end

      def existing_appointment
        appointment_id = params[:id] || params[:appointment_id]
        Appointment.find(appointment_id) if appointment_id.present?
      end

      def load_week_availability(week_start: nil)
        week_availability = Onboarding::CareGuide::WeekAvailability.new(
          care_case: current_care_case,
          member: current_member,
          appointment_type: care_guide_appointment,
          interpretation_language_id: interpretation_language_id,
          existing_appointment: existing_appointment,
          book_with_another_care_guide_modal: book_with_another_care_guide_modal?
        )

        result = week_availability.load(week_start: week_start)

        redirect_to trapdoor and return if result.nil?

        @availability_context = result[:availability_context]
        @slots_by_date_hash = result[:slots_by_date_hash]
        @date = result[:date]
      end
    end
  end
end

module Members
  module Intake
    class AppointmentsController < BaseController
      include UncacheableEndpoints
      include CriticalEndpoints
      include CareCaseScoped

      layout "members/onboarding"
      show_nav_links [:home]

      def create
        track_reservation
        AppointmentReservation.create!(start_time: selected_datetime, staffer: selected_staffer, appointment_type: appointment_type, care_case: current_care_case, interpretation_language: interpretation_language)

        redirect_to Onboarding::IntakeJourney.new(current_care_case).flow.after(:scheduling)
      end

      private

      def selected_datetime
        Time.zone.parse(params.fetch(:appointment_datetime))
      end

      def selected_staffer
        Staffer.find_by(id: params.fetch(:staffer_id))
      end

      def interpretation_language
        Language.find(params[:interpretation_language_id])
      end

      helper_method def appointment_type
        Calendaring::InitialAppointmentType.for_program(current_care_case.program, interpretation_requested: interpretation_language.present?)
      end

      def track_reservation
        if current_care_case.program&.care_guide?
          Analytics::Event::CareGuideBooking::Scheduled.track(
            care_case: current_care_case,
            interpretation_language: interpretation_language&.name,
            appointment_type_id: appointment_type.id,
            selected_datetime: selected_datetime,
            staffer_id: selected_staffer.id
          )
        else
          ahoy_track("IntakeProviderChoiceBooking:Scheduled", care_case_id: current_care_case.id, program_id: current_care_case.program_id, selected_datetime: selected_datetime, selected_staffer: selected_staffer, interpretation_language: interpretation_language)
        end
      end
    end
  end
end

- ✅ Refactored methods for clarity (`fetch_dates`, `group_dates_by_staffer`)
- ✅ Updated `TestDoubles::Acuity` with multi-staffer template stubs
- ✅ Updated specs to use integration-style testing with Acuity-level stubbing

module CareCases
  class AppointmentSchedulingRequestsController < BaseController
    include CareCaseScoped
    include ScheduleAppointmentHelpers

    def new
      @members = CareCaseMember.for(current_care_case, members: care_case_members).sort_by(&:full_name_with_roles)
      @members_with_email = CareCaseMember.for(current_care_case, members: care_case_members.with_email).sort_by(&:full_name_with_roles)
      @covered_by_california = member_experience_configuration&.care_case_covered_by_program?
      @existing_appointment_requests = Calendaring::AppointmentSchedulingRequest.where(care_case: current_care_case).order(created_at: :desc)
    end

    def create
      # the allow_multiple ability is not currently supported on the frontend.
      # we've left it on the model in case we want to re-establish this feature in the future.
      @scheduling_request = Calendaring::AppointmentSchedulingRequest.create!(create_params.merge(care_case: current_care_case))
    end

    private

    def create_params
      params.require(:calendaring_appointment_scheduling_request)
        .except(:include_uncredentialed_staffers)
        .permit(:member_id, :appointment_type_id, :staffer_id, :interpretation_language_id, participant_ids: [])
    end

    def care_case_members
      current_care_case.members_ordered_by_role_name
    end

    helper_method def primary_care_case_member?(member:)
      CareCaseMember.new(care_case: current_care_case, member:).primary_role?
    end

    helper_method def schedule_request_url
      @schedule_request_url ||= members_care_case_appointment_scheduling_request_url(@scheduling_request.care_case, @scheduling_request)
    end

    helper_method def short_link
      ShortLink.find_or_create_by(url: schedule_request_url).short_url_for_members
    end

    helper_method def filter_params
      if params[:calendaring_appointment_scheduling_request]
        params.require(:calendaring_appointment_scheduling_request).permit(:start_date, :member_id, :appointment_type_id, :staffer_id, :include_uncredentialed_staffers, :interpretation_language_id, participant_ids: [])
      else
        {}
      end
    end
  end
end

# frozen_string_literal: true

module Members
  module CareCases
    class AppointmentSchedulingRequestsController < BaseController
      include CareCaseScoped
      include AcuityAppointmentSchedulable

      def show
        redirect_if_not_scheduleable && return unless current_appointment_scheduling_request.scheduleable?
        @availability_data = Calendaring::Appointment::Availability::Data.new(
          date: date,
          slots: available_appointments
        )
      rescue Acuity::Api::Client::Error => e
        render_availability_error(e)
      end

      private

      def initial_request?
        !params[:date].present?
      end

      def date
        @date ||= initial_request? ? first_available_date : Date.parse(params[:date])
      end

      def available_appointments
        Calendaring::AvailableAppointments.new(
          date: date,
          availability_context: availability_context,
          availability_request_reporter: availability_request_reporter
        )
      end

      def availability_context
        Calendaring::AvailabilityContext.new(
          appointment_type: current_appointment_scheduling_request.appointment_type,
          care_case: current_care_case,
          member: current_appointment_scheduling_request.member,
          staffers: [current_appointment_scheduling_request.staffer],
          request_context: Calendaring::AvailabilityRequestContext.appointment_scheduling_request,
          interpretation_language_id: current_appointment_scheduling_request.interpretation_language_id
        )
      end

      def availability_request_reporter
        if initial_request?
          Calendaring::AppointmentAvailabilityRequestReporter.from_availability_context(availability_context)
        else
          Calendaring::NoopAvailabilityRequestReporter.new
        end
      end

      def redirect_if_not_scheduleable
        flash[:error] = helpers.scoped_t(:link_expired)
        redirect_to members_account_family_path(current_care_case.account)
      end

      helper_method def current_appointment_scheduling_request
        @current_appointment_scheduling_request ||= Calendaring::AppointmentSchedulingRequest.where(care_case: current_care_case).find(params[:id])
      end
    end
  end
end

Based on my exploration across branches and the codebase, here's the information for your UAT document:

---

## **Setup Requirements**

### Feature Flags (to turn on in staging)
1. **`use_reef_templates`** - Per-staffer flag to enable Reef templates for availability
   - Enable for Billie Eilish specifically: `Flipper.enable(:use_reef_templates, staffer)`
   - Note: Therapists automatically use templates (code at `app/models/calendaring/api/availability.rb:131-133`)
2. **`reef_template_builder`** - Enables the template builder UI for ops
3. **`blk_catchup_coaching_enablement`** - Enables coaching in templates feature
4. **`blk_catchup_new_patient_limit`** - Enables new patient limits for templates

### Migrations
All template migrations are already in main (dated 2025-08-16 to 2025-10-16):
- `calendaring_templates`, `calendaring_template_regular_hours`, `calendaring_template_blocks`
- `calendaring_template_block_types`, `calendaring_template_block_type_appointment_types`
- `calendaring_template_published_appointment_type_times`, `calendaring_template_recurring_time_slots`

### Required PRs

| PR | Title | Status |
|-----|-------|--------|
| #17893 | TB-1867: Add coaching capability to templates | ✅ Merged |
| #17902 | TB-1896: Add care guide capability to templates | ✅ Merged |
| #17905 | TB-1869: Migrate AvailableStaffers to new Calendaring API | ✅ Merged |
| #17911 | TB-1870: Remove CoachSwap self-serve UI | ✅ Merged |
| #17924 | TB-1871: Unifies care case scheduling (BLK/Clinic) | ✅ Merged |
| #17906 | TB-1870: Migrate member availability to Calendaring::Api | ⏳ Open |
| #17922 | TB-1868: Migrate WeekAvailability to Calendaring API | ⏳ Open |

**Note:** PRs #17906 and #17922 must merge for full member-facing template support.

---

## **Test Accounts (to fill in)**

| Role | Actor | Credentials |
|------|-------|-------------|
| Care guide | (Need staging staffer with care_guide capability) | TBD |
| Member | (Need member with BLK care case in staging) | TBD |

---

## **Detailed Test Cases 5-10**

### Test case 5: Book a coaching intake as a member
**Member:**
1. Go to member staging: https://member.staging-hellobrightline.com
2. Log in as a member with an active BrightLife Kids care case
3. Complete intake assessment if not already done
4. On provider choice screen, select a coaching appointment time
5. Confirm the availability matches the template set up for the coach
6. Complete booking and verify confirmation

### Test case 6: Book a care guide intake as a member
**Member:**
1. Log in to member portal
2. Navigate to care case → Intake flow
3. Go through to care guide scheduling (`/intake/care_guide_appointments/new`)
4. Select interpretation language if needed
5. Select available time slot from care guide's template
6. Confirm booking

### Test case 7: Reschedule a coaching intake as a member
**Member:**
1. Log in with a member that has a scheduled coaching intake
2. Go to Appointments page (`/appointments`)
3. Click on the scheduled coaching appointment
4. Click "Reschedule" (note: not available within 24 hours of appointment)
5. Select new time from coach's template availability
6. Confirm rescheduling

### Test case 8: Reschedule a coaching ongoing session as a member
**Member:**
1. Log in with a member that has a scheduled coaching session (non-intake)
2. Go to Appointments page
3. Click on the coaching session
4. Click "Reschedule" 
5. Verify availability shows times matching coach's template
6. Select new time and confirm

### Test case 9: Reschedule a care guide session as a member
**Member:**
1. Log in with a member with a scheduled care guide session
2. Go to Appointments → Select the care guide appointment
3. Click edit/reschedule (`/intake/care_guide_appointments/:id/edit`)
4. Choose new available time
5. Confirm the rescheduled appointment

### Test case 10: Create a self-scheduling link for a coaching appointment
**MS (Staffer):**
1. Log in to Reef as a staffer with scheduling permissions
2. Go to a care case with BLK program
3. Click "Create Appointment Link" or go to scheduling requests
4. Select:
   - Member for the appointment
   - Appointment type: Coaching Session or Coaching - Welcome Session
   - Staffer: Select the coach with Reef template
   - Language interpretation (optional)
5. Generate the self-scheduling link
6. Copy and share the link with member

**Member:**
7. Open the shared link
8. Confirm availability displayed matches the coach's template
9. Select a time and book the appointment

---

Let me know if you need any additional details or want me to dig deeper into specific areas!

Good catch. Here's the **complete list of feature flags** needed for Templates UAT:

| Flag | Purpose | Where Used |
|------|---------|------------|
| `use_reef_templates` | Enable templates for non-therapist staffers (per-staffer) | `Calendaring::Api::Availability` - routes availability through templates |
| `reef_template_builder` | Show Templates tab in Staffing menu for ops | `TabHelpers`, `TemplatesController` |
| `blk_catchup_coaching_enablement` | Enable coaching capability in templates feature | `TemplatesController`, `RootAppointmentType` |
| `blk_catchup_new_patient_limit` | Enable new patient limits for BLK staffers | `NewPatientLimit` |
| `blk_unified_scheduling_view` | Use unified scheduling view for BLK care cases | `Staffers::CareCases::AvailabilitiesController` |

So there are **5 feature flags** total, not 4. The `blk_unified_scheduling_view` is new (added 2025-12-09) and controls whether the staffer scheduling UI uses the unified view for BLK care models.
